aiomysql (0.2.0-0ubuntu1~ppa1~noble1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of aiomysql 0.2.0 for the Avalan PPA.
  * Noble ships 0.1.1 (below Avalan's floor) and Debian sid ships
    0.3.2 (above Avalan's ceiling), so the rebuild pins the 0.2.0
    sdist.
  * Ship a quilt patch (relax-build-system-requires) that drops the
    `setuptools_scm[toml] < 7` upper bound and the obsolete standalone
    `setuptools_scm_git_archive` plugin -- both predate setuptools-scm 8
    integrating the git-archive support into the main package, which
    is what Noble actually ships.

 -- Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>  Mon, 18 May 2026 19:45:00 -0300
